{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":80,"text":"Cyndi Stivers: So, future of storytelling."},{"time":2160,"text":"Before we do the future,"},{"time":4000,"text":"let's talk about what is never\ngoing to change about storytelling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7920,"text":"Shonda Rhimes:\nWhat's never going to change."},{"time":10040,"text":"Obviously, I think good stories\nare never going to change,"},{"time":12800,"text":"the need for people to gather together\nand exchange their stories"},{"time":16600,"text":"and to talk about the things\nthat feel universal,"},{"time":19840,"text":"the idea that we all feel\na compelling need to watch stories,"},{"time":22800,"text":"to tell stories, to share stories --"},{"time":26000,"text":"sort of the gathering around the campfire"},{"time":28000,"text":"to discuss the things\nthat tell each one of us"},{"time":30320,"text":"that we are not alone in the world."},{"time":32880,"text":"Those things to me\nare never going to change."},{"time":35040,"text":"That essence of storytelling\nis never going to change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38880,"text":"CS: OK. In preparation\nfor this conversation,"},{"time":41760,"text":"I checked in with Susan Lyne,"},{"time":43680,"text":"who was running ABC Entertainment"},{"time":45800,"text":"when you were working\non \"Grey's Anatomy\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":48600,"text":"SR: Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49840,"text":"CS: And she said that there was\nthis indelible memory she had"},{"time":52760,"text":"of your casting process,"},{"time":54760,"text":"where without discussing it\nwith any of the executives,"},{"time":57440,"text":"you got people coming in\nto read for your scripts,"},{"time":59840,"text":"and every one of them\nwas the full range of humanity,"},{"time":63960,"text":"you did not type anyone in any way,"},{"time":67240,"text":"and that it was completely surprising."},{"time":70080,"text":"So she said, in addition\nto retraining the studio executives,"},{"time":74760,"text":"you also, she feels,"},{"time":76880,"text":"and I think this is -- I agree,"},{"time":79440,"text":"retrained the expectations\nof the American TV audience."},{"time":84360,"text":"So what else does the audience\nnot yet realize that it needs?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90480,"text":"SR: What else does it not yet realize?"},{"time":92360,"text":"Well, I mean, I don't think\nwe're anywhere near there yet."},{"time":95520,"text":"I mean, we're still in a place"},{"time":97280,"text":"in which we're far, far behind what looks\nlike the real world in actuality."},{"time":104240,"text":"I wasn't bringing in\na bunch of actors"},{"time":107960,"text":"who looked very different from one another"},{"time":110600,"text":"simply because I was\ntrying to make a point,"},{"time":112720,"text":"and I wasn't trying\nto do anything special."},{"time":115080,"text":"It never occurred to me\nthat that was new, different or weird."},{"time":119080,"text":"I just brought in actors\nbecause I thought they were interesting"},{"time":122160,"text":"and to me, the idea that it\nwas completely surprising to everybody --"},{"time":126000,"text":"I didn't know that for a while."},{"time":128199,"text":"I just thought: these are the actors\nI want to see play these parts."},{"time":131440,"text":"I want to see what\nthey look like if they read."},{"time":133680,"text":"We'll see what happens."},{"time":134960,"text":"So I think the interesting thing\nthat happens is"},{"time":138360,"text":"that when you look at the world\nthrough another lens,"},{"time":140920,"text":"when you're not the person\nnormally in charge of things,"},{"time":145200,"text":"it just comes out a different way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148400,"text":"CS: So you now have\nthis big machine that you run,"},{"time":152840,"text":"as a titan -- as you know,\nlast year when she gave her talk --"},{"time":155880,"text":"she's a titan."},{"time":157840,"text":"So what do you think\nis going to happen as we go on?"},{"time":161240,"text":"There's a huge amount of money\ninvolved in producing these shows."},{"time":166160,"text":"While the tools of making stories\nhave gone and gotten greatly democratized,"},{"time":172400,"text":"there's still this large distribution:"},{"time":174960,"text":"people who rent networks,\nwho rent the audience to advertisers"},{"time":180080,"text":"and make it all pay."},{"time":181800,"text":"How do you see the business model changing\nnow that anyone can be a storyteller?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":187040,"text":"SR: I think it's changing every day."},{"time":188800,"text":"I mean, the rapid, rapid change\nthat's happening is amazing."},{"time":191760,"text":"And I feel -- the panic is palpable,"},{"time":195120,"text":"and I don't mean that in a bad way."},{"time":196960,"text":"I think it's kind of exciting."},{"time":198640,"text":"The idea that there's\nsort of an equalizer happening,"},{"time":203320,"text":"that sort of means that anybody\ncan make something, is wonderful."},{"time":207120,"text":"I think there's some scary in the idea\nthat you can't find the good work now."},{"time":212880,"text":"There's so much work out there."},{"time":214400,"text":"I think there's something like\n417 dramas on television right now"},{"time":217520,"text":"at any given time in any given place,"},{"time":220080,"text":"but you can't find them."},{"time":221360,"text":"You can't find the good ones."},{"time":222800,"text":"So there's a lot of bad stuff out there\nbecause everybody can make something."},{"time":226480,"text":"It's like if everybody painted a painting."},{"time":228520,"text":"You know, there's not\nthat many good painters."},{"time":231040,"text":"But finding the good stories,\nthe good shows,"},{"time":234080,"text":"is harder and harder and harder."},{"time":235680,"text":"Because if you have\none tiny show over here on AMC"},{"time":238320,"text":"and one tiny show over here over there,"},{"time":240240,"text":"finding where they are\nbecomes much harder."},{"time":242600,"text":"So I think that ferreting out the gems"},{"time":244480,"text":"and finding out who made\nthe great webisode and who made this,"},{"time":247600,"text":"it's -- I mean, think\nabout the poor critics"},{"time":249720,"text":"who now are spending 24 hours a day"},{"time":251440,"text":"trapped in their homes\nwatching everything."},{"time":253520,"text":"It's not an easy job right now."},{"time":255640,"text":"So the distribution engines\nare getting more and more vast,"},{"time":259240,"text":"but finding the good programming\nfor everybody in the audience"},{"time":262200,"text":"is getting harder."},{"time":263440,"text":"And unlike the news,"},{"time":265240,"text":"where everything's getting\nwinnowed down to just who you are,"},{"time":268800,"text":"television seems to be getting --"},{"time":270440,"text":"and by television I mean anything\nyou can watch, television shows on --"},{"time":274400,"text":"seems to be getting\nwider and wider and wider."},{"time":276640,"text":"And so anybody's making stories,"},{"time":279320,"text":"and the geniuses are sometimes hidden."},{"time":281640,"text":"But it's going to be harder to find,"},{"time":284440,"text":"and at some point that will collapse."},{"time":286480,"text":"People keep talking about peak TV."},{"time":288240,"text":"I don't know when that's going to happen."},{"time":290240,"text":"I think at some point\nit'll collapse a little bit"},{"time":292720,"text":"and we'll, sort of, come back together."},{"time":294640,"text":"I don't know if it\nwill be network television."},{"time":296840,"text":"I don't know if that model is sustainable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299440,"text":"CS: What about the model"},{"time":301000,"text":"that Amazon and Netflix are throwing\na lot of money around right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307520,"text":"SR: That is true."},{"time":309840,"text":"I think it's an interesting model."},{"time":311520,"text":"I think there's\nsomething exciting about it."},{"time":313640,"text":"For content creators, I think\nthere's something exciting about it."},{"time":316800,"text":"For the world, I think\nthere's something exciting about it."},{"time":319560,"text":"The idea that there are programs now"},{"time":321320,"text":"that can be in multiple languages\nwith characters from all over the world"},{"time":324800,"text":"that are appealing and come out\nfor everybody at the same time"},{"time":327800,"text":"is exciting."},{"time":329240,"text":"I mean, I think the international sense\nthat television can now take on"},{"time":333760,"text":"makes sense to me,"},{"time":335000,"text":"that programming can now take on."},{"time":336640,"text":"Television so much is made for, like --\nhere's our American audience."},{"time":339920,"text":"We make these shows,"},{"time":341200,"text":"and then they shove them\nout into the world"},{"time":343240,"text":"and hope for the best,"},{"time":344560,"text":"as opposed to really thinking\nabout the fact that America is not it."},{"time":348520,"text":"I mean, we love ourselves\nand everything, but it's not i."},{"time":351280,"text":"And we should be\ntaking into account the fact"},{"time":354480,"text":"that there are all\nof these other places in the world"},{"time":357000,"text":"that we should be interested in\nwhile we're telling stories."},{"time":360040,"text":"It makes the world smaller."},{"time":363520,"text":"I don't know."},{"time":364760,"text":"I think it pushes forward the idea\nthat the world is a universal place,"},{"time":369760,"text":"and our stories become universal things."},{"time":371720,"text":"We stop being other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373640,"text":"CS: You've pioneered, as far as I can see,"},{"time":377480,"text":"interesting ways to launch new shows, too."},{"time":380120,"text":"I mean, when you\nlaunched \"Scandal\" in 2012,"},{"time":383160,"text":"there was this amazing groundswell\nof support on Twitter"},{"time":386640,"text":"the likes of which nobody had seen before."},{"time":389800,"text":"Do you have any other\ntricks up your sleeve"},{"time":392240,"text":"when you launch your next one?"},{"time":394400,"text":"What do you think\nwill happen in that regard?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":396560,"text":"SR: We do have some interesting ideas."},{"time":399040,"text":"We have a show called \"Still Star-Crossed\"\ncoming out this summer."},{"time":402200,"text":"We have some interesting ideas for that."},{"time":404160,"text":"I'm not sure if we're going\nto be able to do them in time."},{"time":406920,"text":"I thought they were fun."},{"time":408160,"text":"But the idea\nthat we would live-tweet our show"},{"time":410360,"text":"was really just us thinking\nthat would be fun."},{"time":412560,"text":"We didn't realize that the critics\nwould start to live-tweet along with us."},{"time":416120,"text":"But the fans -- getting people\nto be a part of it,"},{"time":418520,"text":"making it more of a campfire --"},{"time":420080,"text":"you know, when you're all\non Twitter together"},{"time":422240,"text":"and you're all talking together,"},{"time":423840,"text":"it is more of a shared experience,"},{"time":425520,"text":"and finding other ways\nto make that possible"},{"time":427680,"text":"and finding other ways\nto make people feel engaged"},{"time":430040,"text":"is important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432320,"text":"CS: So when you have\nall those different people making stories"},{"time":436960,"text":"and only some of them\nare going to break through"},{"time":439280,"text":"and get that audience somehow,"},{"time":441080,"text":"how do you think\nstorytellers will get paid?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":444080,"text":"SR: I actually have been struggling\nwith this concept as well."},{"time":447040,"text":"Is it going to be a subscriber model?"},{"time":449160,"text":"Are people going to say, like, I'm going\nto watch this particular person's shows,"},{"time":453840,"text":"and that's how we're going to do it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":455600,"text":"CS: I think we should buy\na passport to Shondaland. Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":458360,"text":"SR: I don't know about that, but yeah.\nThat's a lot more work for me."},{"time":461640,"text":"I do think that there are\ngoing to be different ways,"},{"time":464480,"text":"but I don't know necessarily."},{"time":466000,"text":"I mean, I'll be honest and say\na lot of content creators"},{"time":468680,"text":"are not necessarily interested\nin being distributors,"},{"time":472120,"text":"mainly because what I dream of doing"},{"time":475360,"text":"is creating content."},{"time":476800,"text":"I really love to create content."},{"time":478680,"text":"I want to get paid for it"},{"time":479920,"text":"and I want to get paid the money\nthat I deserve to get paid for it,"},{"time":483120,"text":"and there's a hard part in finding that."},{"time":485080,"text":"But I also want it to be made possible"},{"time":487640,"text":"for, you know,\nthe people who work with me,"},{"time":490640,"text":"the people who work for me,"},{"time":492000,"text":"everybody to sort of get paid in a way,\nand they're all making a living."},{"time":495400,"text":"How it gets distributed\nis getting harder and harder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500000,"text":"CS: How about the many new tools,"},{"time":502640,"text":"you know, VR, AR ..."},{"time":505880,"text":"I find it fascinating\nthat you can't really binge-watch,"},{"time":509920,"text":"you can't fast-forward in those things."},{"time":513200,"text":"What do you see as the future\nof those for storytelling?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":516360,"text":"SR: I spent a lot of time in the past year"},{"time":519120,"text":"just exploring those,"},{"time":520720,"text":"getting lots of demonstrations\nand paying attention."},{"time":523400,"text":"I find them fascinating,"},{"time":525240,"text":"mainly because I think that --"},{"time":527240,"text":"I think most people\nthink of them for gaming,"},{"time":529560,"text":"I think most people think of them\nfor things like action,"},{"time":532280,"text":"and I think that there is\na sense of intimacy"},{"time":534960,"text":"that is very present in those things,"},{"time":538880,"text":"the idea that -- picture this,"},{"time":541400,"text":"you can sit there\nand have a conversation with Fitz,"},{"time":544920,"text":"or at least sit there\nwhile Fitz talks to you,"},{"time":547120,"text":"President Fitzgerald Grant III,"},{"time":549040,"text":"while he talks to you"},{"time":550360,"text":"about why he's making\na choice that he makes,"},{"time":552520,"text":"and it's a very heartfelt moment."},{"time":554160,"text":"And instead of you watching\na television screen,"},{"time":556760,"text":"you're sitting there next to him,\nand he's having this conversation."},{"time":560000,"text":"Now, you fall in love with the man"},{"time":561680,"text":"while he's doing it\nfrom a television screen."},{"time":563840,"text":"Imagine sitting next to him,"},{"time":565240,"text":"or being with a character like Huck\nwho's about to execute somebody."},{"time":569320,"text":"And instead of having a scene"},{"time":570840,"text":"where, you know, he's talking\nto another character very rapidly,"},{"time":574680,"text":"he goes into a closet and turns to you\nand tells you, you know,"},{"time":578080,"text":"what's going to happen\nand why he's afraid and nervous."},{"time":580720,"text":"It's a little more like theater,\nand I'm not sure it would work,"},{"time":583760,"text":"but I'm fascinating by the concept\nof something like that"},{"time":586480,"text":"and what that would mean for an audience."},{"time":588480,"text":"And to get to play with those ideas\nwould be interesting,"},{"time":591200,"text":"and I think, you know, for my audience,\nthe people who watch my shows,"},{"time":595640,"text":"which is, you know, women 12 to 75,"},{"time":597960,"text":"there's something interesting\nin there for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602720,"text":"CS: And how about\nthe input of the audience?"},{"time":605520,"text":"How interested are you in the things"},{"time":607360,"text":"where the audience\ncan actually go up to a certain point"},{"time":610520,"text":"and then decide, oh wait,\nI'm going to choose my own adventure."},{"time":614200,"text":"I'm going to run off with Fitz\nor I'm going to run off with --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":617160,"text":"SR: Oh, the choose-\nyour-own-adventure stories."},{"time":619400,"text":"I have a hard time with those,"},{"time":620880,"text":"and not necessarily because\nI want to be in control of everything,"},{"time":624040,"text":"but because when I'm watching television\nor I'm watching a movie,"},{"time":627440,"text":"I know for a fact\nthat a story is not as good"},{"time":632280,"text":"when I have control\nover exactly what's going to happen"},{"time":635080,"text":"to somebody else's character."},{"time":636840,"text":"You know, if I could tell you exactly\nwhat I wanted to happen to Walter White,"},{"time":640640,"text":"that's great, but the story\nis not the same, and it's not as powerful."},{"time":644240,"text":"You know, if I'm in charge\nof how \"The Sopranos\" ends,"},{"time":646840,"text":"then that's lovely and I have an ending\nthat's nice and satisfying,"},{"time":650040,"text":"but it's not the same story\nand it's not the same emotional impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653240,"text":"CS: I can't stop imagining\nwhat that might be."},{"time":656640,"text":"Sorry, you're losing me for a minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658480,"text":"SR: But what's wonderful is\nI don't get to imagine it,"},{"time":661080,"text":"because Vince has his own ending,"},{"time":663240,"text":"and it makes it really powerful\nto know that somebody else has told."},{"time":666800,"text":"You know, if you could\ndecide that, you know,"},{"time":669080,"text":"in \"Jaws,\" the shark wins or something,"},{"time":671320,"text":"it doesn't do what it needs to do for you."},{"time":674440,"text":"The story is the story that is told,"},{"time":676179,"text":"and you can walk away angry\nand you can walk away debating"},{"time":678920,"text":"and you can walk away arguing,"},{"time":680400,"text":"but that's why it works."},{"time":682280,"text":"That is why it's art."},{"time":683560,"text":"Otherwise, it's just a game,"},{"time":685400,"text":"and games can be art,\nbut in a very different way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688440,"text":"CS: Gamers who actually\nsell the right to sit there"},{"time":692040,"text":"and comment on what's happening,"},{"time":694200,"text":"to me that's more community\nthan storytelling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697200,"text":"SR: And that is its own form of campfire."},{"time":699200,"text":"I don't discount that\nas a form of storytelling,"},{"time":702360,"text":"but it is a group form, I suppose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706200,"text":"CS: All right,\nwhat about the super-super --"},{"time":709680,"text":"the fact that everything's\ngetting shorter, shorter, shorter."},{"time":712920,"text":"And, you know, Snapchat\nnow has something it calls shows"},{"time":716200,"text":"that are one minute long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719080,"text":"SR: It's interesting."},{"time":722880,"text":"Part of me thinks\nit sounds like commercials."},{"time":726320,"text":"I mean, it does -- like, sponsored by."},{"time":729120,"text":"But part of me also gets it completely."},{"time":731760,"text":"There's something\nreally wonderful about it."},{"time":733880,"text":"If you think about a world"},{"time":735200,"text":"in which most people\nare watching television on their phones,"},{"time":738120,"text":"if you think about a place like India,"},{"time":740000,"text":"where most of the input is coming in"},{"time":741760,"text":"and that's where\nmost of the product is coming in,"},{"time":744160,"text":"shorter makes sense."},{"time":745440,"text":"If you can charge people more\nfor shorter periods of content,"},{"time":749000,"text":"some distributor has figured out\na way to make a lot more money."},{"time":752280,"text":"If you're making content,"},{"time":754320,"text":"it costs less money\nto make it and put it out there."},{"time":757240,"text":"And, by the way,"},{"time":758480,"text":"if you're 14 and have\na short attention span, like my daughter,"},{"time":763000,"text":"that's what you want to see,\nthat's what you want to make,"},{"time":765760,"text":"that's how it works."},{"time":767000,"text":"And if you do it right\nand it actually feels like narrative,"},{"time":771240,"text":"people will hang on for it\nno matter what you do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774560,"text":"CS: I'm glad you raised your daughters,"},{"time":776480,"text":"because I am wondering how are they\ngoing to consume entertainment,"},{"time":781320,"text":"and also not just entertainment,"},{"time":783600,"text":"but news, too."},{"time":785960,"text":"When they're not -- I mean,\nthe algorithmic robot overlords"},{"time":788960,"text":"are going to feed them\nwhat they've already done."},{"time":792080,"text":"How do you think we will correct for that\nand make people well-rounded citizens?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":797760,"text":"SR: Well, me and how I correct for it"},{"time":799960,"text":"is completely different\nthan how somebody else might do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802760,"text":"CS: Feel free to speculate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804880,"text":"SR: I really don't know\nhow we're going to do it in the future."},{"time":807880,"text":"I mean, my poor children have been\nthe subject of all of my experiments."},{"time":811320,"text":"We're still doing\nwhat I call \"Amish summers\""},{"time":813720,"text":"where I turn off all electronics"},{"time":815480,"text":"and pack away\nall their computers and stuff"},{"time":817560,"text":"and watch them scream for a while\nuntil they settle down"},{"time":820560,"text":"into, like, an electronic-free summer."},{"time":824280,"text":"But honestly, it's a very hard world"},{"time":827000,"text":"in which now, as grown-ups,"},{"time":829040,"text":"we're so interested\nin watching our own thing,"},{"time":832200,"text":"and we don't even know\nthat we're being fed, sometimes,"},{"time":835400,"text":"just our own opinions."},{"time":837160,"text":"You know, the way it's working now,"},{"time":838880,"text":"you're watching a feed,"},{"time":840160,"text":"and the feeds are being corrected"},{"time":841800,"text":"so that you're only getting\nyour own opinions"},{"time":843960,"text":"and you're feeling\nmore and more right about yourself."},{"time":846520,"text":"So how do you really start to discern?"},{"time":848400,"text":"It's getting a little bit disturbing."},{"time":850240,"text":"So maybe it'll overcorrect,\nmaybe it'll all explode,"},{"time":853080,"text":"or maybe we'll all just become --"},{"time":856080,"text":"I hate to be negative about it,"},{"time":857640,"text":"but maybe we'll all\njust become more idiotic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861600,"text":"(Cyndi laughs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":863360,"text":"CS: Yeah, can you picture\nany corrective that you could do"},{"time":866800,"text":"with scripted, fictional work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":869720,"text":"SR: I think a lot about the fact\nthat television has the power"},{"time":873400,"text":"to educate people in a powerful way,"},{"time":875160,"text":"and when you're watching television --"},{"time":877040,"text":"for instance, they do studies\nabout medical shows."},{"time":880320,"text":"I think it's 87 percent,\n87 percent of people"},{"time":882480,"text":"get most of their knowledge\nabout medicine and medical facts"},{"time":885880,"text":"from medical shows,"},{"time":887360,"text":"much more so than\nthey do from their doctors,"},{"time":889520,"text":"than from articles."},{"time":890920,"text":"So we work really hard to be accurate,\nand every time we make a mistake,"},{"time":894360,"text":"I feel really guilty,\nlike we're going to do something bad,"},{"time":897200,"text":"but we also give a lot\nof good medical information."},{"time":899880,"text":"There are so many other ways\nto give information on those shows."},{"time":902960,"text":"People are being entertained"},{"time":904360,"text":"and maybe they don't want\nto read the news,"},{"time":906440,"text":"but there are a lot of ways to give\nfair information out on those shows,"},{"time":909880,"text":"not in some creepy, like,\nwe're going to control people's minds way,"},{"time":914520,"text":"but in a way that's sort of\nvery interesting and intelligent"},{"time":917400,"text":"and not about pushing\none side's version or the other,"},{"time":920880,"text":"like, giving out the truth."},{"time":922240,"text":"It would be strange, though,"},{"time":924200,"text":"if television drama\nwas how we were giving the news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927960,"text":"CS: It would be strange,"},{"time":929240,"text":"but I gather a lot of what\nyou've written as fiction"},{"time":932480,"text":"has become prediction this season?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":935560,"text":"SR: You know, \"Scandal\" has been\nvery disturbing for that reason."},{"time":938840,"text":"We have this show\nthat's about politics gone mad,"},{"time":941840,"text":"and basically the way\nwe've always told the show --"},{"time":944800,"text":"you know, everybody\npays attention to the papers."},{"time":947200,"text":"We read everything.\nWe talk about everything."},{"time":949360,"text":"We have lots of friends in Washington."},{"time":951320,"text":"And we'd always sort of\ndone our show as a speculation."},{"time":954200,"text":"We'd sit in the room and think,"},{"time":955720,"text":"what would happen\nif the wheels came off the bus"},{"time":958000,"text":"and everything went crazy?"},{"time":959320,"text":"And that was always great,"},{"time":960880,"text":"except now it felt like\nthe wheels were coming off the bus"},{"time":963840,"text":"and things were actually going crazy,"},{"time":965680,"text":"so the things that we were speculating\nwere really coming true."},{"time":968680,"text":"I mean, our season this year"},{"time":970080,"text":"was going to end with the Russians\ncontrolling the American election,"},{"time":973880,"text":"and we'd written it, we'd planned for it,"},{"time":976560,"text":"it was all there,"},{"time":977800,"text":"and then the Russians were suspected\nof being involved in the American election"},{"time":981640,"text":"and we suddenly had to change\nwhat we were going to do for our season."},{"time":985000,"text":"I walked in and I was like,"},{"time":986360,"text":"\"That scene where our mystery woman\nstarts speaking Russian?"},{"time":989240,"text":"We have to fix that\nand figure out what we're going to do.\""},{"time":992120,"text":"That just comes from extrapolating"},{"time":993800,"text":"out from what we thought\nwas going to happen,"},{"time":996040,"text":"or what we thought was crazy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998520,"text":"CS: That's great."},{"time":999840,"text":"So where else in US or elsewhere\nin the world do you look?"},{"time":1004760,"text":"Who is doing interesting\nstorytelling right now?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007240,"text":"SR: I don't know, there's a lot\nof interesting stuff out there."},{"time":1010280,"text":"Obviously British television\nis always amazing"},{"time":1013240,"text":"and always does interesting things."},{"time":1015880,"text":"I don't get to watch a lot of TV,"},{"time":1018200,"text":"mainly because I'm busy working."},{"time":1020640,"text":"And I pretty much try not to watch\nvery much television at all,"},{"time":1024280,"text":"even American television,\nuntil I'm done with a season,"},{"time":1027200,"text":"because things start\nto creep into my head otherwise."},{"time":1029720,"text":"I start to wonder, like,"},{"time":1031680,"text":"why can't our characters wear crowns\nand talk about being on a throne?"},{"time":1035119,"text":"It gets crazy."},{"time":1036800,"text":"So I try not to watch much\nuntil the seasons are over."},{"time":1040560,"text":"But I do think that there's a lot of\ninteresting European television out there."},{"time":1044319,"text":"I was at the International Emmys"},{"time":1046240,"text":"and looking around and seeing\nthe stuff that they were showing,"},{"time":1049240,"text":"and I was kind of fascinated."},{"time":1050680,"text":"There's some stuff\nI want to watch and check out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053440,"text":"CS: Can you imagine --"},{"time":1054720,"text":"I know that you don't spend a lot of time\nthinking about tech stuff,"},{"time":1058280,"text":"but you know how a few years ago\nwe had someone here at TED"},{"time":1061320,"text":"talking about seeing,"},{"time":1063600,"text":"wearing Google Glass and seeing\nyour TV shows essentially in your eye?"},{"time":1069760,"text":"Do you ever fantasize when, you know --"},{"time":1072080,"text":"the little girl\nwho sat on the pantry floor"},{"time":1074560,"text":"in your parents' house,"},{"time":1076320,"text":"did you ever imagine any other medium?"},{"time":1080200,"text":"Or would you now?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081680,"text":"SR: Any other medium."},{"time":1083040,"text":"For storytelling, other than books?"},{"time":1084760,"text":"I mean, I grew up wanting\nto be Toni Morrison, so no."},{"time":1087600,"text":"I mean, I didn't even imagine television."},{"time":1089600,"text":"So the idea that there could be\nsome bigger world,"},{"time":1093480,"text":"some more magical way of making things ---"},{"time":1095680,"text":"I'm always excited\nwhen new technology comes out"},{"time":1097960,"text":"and I'm always the first one\nto want to try it."},{"time":1101000,"text":"The possibilities feel endless\nand exciting right now,"},{"time":1104200,"text":"which is what excites me."},{"time":1107040,"text":"We're in this sort of Wild West period,\nto me, it feels like,"},{"time":1110120,"text":"because nobody knows\nwhat we're going to settle on."},{"time":1112560,"text":"You can put stories anywhere right now"},{"time":1114800,"text":"and that's cool to me,"},{"time":1116280,"text":"and it feels like once we figure out\nhow to get the technology"},{"time":1120440,"text":"and the creativity\nof storytelling to meet,"},{"time":1123920,"text":"the possibilities are endless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1126280,"text":"CS: And also the technology has enabled\nthe thing I briefly flew by earlier,"},{"time":1131040,"text":"binge-viewing,\nwhich is a recent phenomenon,"},{"time":1134040,"text":"since you've been doing shows, right?"},{"time":1136240,"text":"And how do you think does that change\nthe storytelling process at all?"},{"time":1140960,"text":"You always had a bible\nfor the whole season beforehand, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1144800,"text":"SR: No, I just always knew\nwhere we were going to end."},{"time":1148160,"text":"So for me,"},{"time":1150520,"text":"the only way I can really comment on that"},{"time":1152520,"text":"is that I have a show\nthat's been going on for 14 seasons"},{"time":1157240,"text":"and so there are the people\nwho have been watching it for 14 seasons,"},{"time":1160560,"text":"and then there are the 12-year-old girls\nI'd encounter in the grocery store"},{"time":1164120,"text":"who had watched\n297 episodes in three weeks."},{"time":1168120,"text":"Seriously, and that's a very different\nexperience for them,"},{"time":1170960,"text":"because they've been inside of something"},{"time":1172920,"text":"really intensely for\na very short period of time"},{"time":1176360,"text":"in a very intense way,"},{"time":1177880,"text":"and to them the story\nhas a completely different arc"},{"time":1180840,"text":"and a completely different meaning"},{"time":1182520,"text":"because it never had any breaks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1184120,"text":"CS: It's like visiting a country\nand then leaving it. It's a strange --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1187480,"text":"SR: It's like reading an amazing novel\nand then putting it down."},{"time":1190560,"text":"I think that is the beauty\nof the experience."},{"time":1193640,"text":"You don't necessarily have to watch\nsomething for 14 seasons."},{"time":1196600,"text":"It's not necessarily\nthe way everything's supposed to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1200320,"text":"CS: Is there any topic\nthat you don't think we should touch?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1204600,"text":"SR: I don't think\nI think of story that way."},{"time":1206800,"text":"I think of story in terms of character\nand what characters would do"},{"time":1210000,"text":"and what characters need to do\nin order to make them move forward,"},{"time":1213240,"text":"so I'm never really thinking of story\nin terms of just plot,"},{"time":1216440,"text":"and when writers come\ninto my writer's room and pitch me plot,"},{"time":1219400,"text":"I say, \"You're not speaking English.\""},{"time":1221520,"text":"Like, that's the thing I say."},{"time":1222960,"text":"We're not speaking English.\nI need to hear what's real."},{"time":1225600,"text":"And so I don't think of it that way."},{"time":1227360,"text":"I don't know if there's a way\nto think there's something I wouldn't do"},{"time":1230720,"text":"because that feels like I'm plucking\npieces of plot off a wall or something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1234360,"text":"CS: That's great. To what extent\ndo you think you will use --"},{"time":1237520,"text":"You know, you recently went\non the board of Planned Parenthood"},{"time":1240480,"text":"and got involved\nin the Hillary Clinton campaign."},{"time":1243200,"text":"To what extent do you think\nyou will use your storytelling"},{"time":1246840,"text":"in the real world"},{"time":1248600,"text":"to effect change?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1252000,"text":"SR: Well, you know, there's --"},{"time":1255320,"text":"That's an intense subject to me,"},{"time":1256920,"text":"because I feel like the lack of narrative"},{"time":1259720,"text":"that a lot of people have is difficult."},{"time":1265720,"text":"You know, like,\nthere's a lot of organizations"},{"time":1267920,"text":"that don't have a positive narrative\nthat they've created for themselves"},{"time":1271960,"text":"that would help them."},{"time":1274000,"text":"There's a lot of campaigns"},{"time":1275840,"text":"that could be helped\nwith a better narrative."},{"time":1279480,"text":"The Democrats could do a lot"},{"time":1282000,"text":"with a very strong\nnarrative for themselves."},{"time":1284120,"text":"There's a lot of different things\nthat could happen"},{"time":1286560,"text":"in terms of using storytelling voice,"},{"time":1288400,"text":"and I don't mean that in a fiction way,"},{"time":1290320,"text":"I mean that in a same way\nthat any speechwriter would mean it."},{"time":1294480,"text":"And I see that,"},{"time":1295720,"text":"but I don't necessarily know\nthat that's, like, my job to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1299920,"text":"CS: All right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1301160,"text":"Please help me thank Shonda.\nSR: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1303800,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}